.TH man 1 "April 13, 2021" "0.4.2" "HSH"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
- a rudimentary command-line interpreter (UNIX)
.br
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.br
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a command-line interpreter that executes
.br
commands read from the standard input or from a file.
.br
It can be used in interactive or non-interactive mode.
.PP
For interactive mode launch the executable as follows:
\f[B]\&./hsh\f[].
.br
It will display the prompt: \f[B]$ \f[].
Then it will read any input and execute
.br
any passed commands.
.PP
For non-interactive mode use a shell script to
.br
redirect with a pipeline (\f[B]|\f[])
.br
Note: you must specify the name or the path of the command to be
.br
passed to \f[B]\&./hsh\f[]
.br
.SH BUILT-IN OPTIONS
.B Ctrl+D
: Exits interactive mode.
.br
.B env
: Displays environmental variables.
.br
.B exit
: Exits program entirely.
.br
.SH EXAMPLE
.br
$ ./hsh
.br
($) /bin/ls
.br
($) hsh main.c shell.c
.br
($) exit
.br
$
.br
.br
.SH BUGS
No known bugs
.br
.SH AUTHORS
Gabriel Vazquez and Gabriela Martinez
